<score-partwise>
  <work>
    <work-title>Were You There?</work-title>
  </work>
  <identification>
    <creator type="composer">Words: African-American Spiritual, before 1899.
Music: 'Were You There' African-American Spiritual, before 1899.  Setting: attr. Charles Winfred Douglas, 1940.
copyright: public domain.  This score is a part of the Open Hymnal Project, 2013 Revision.</creator>
    <encoding>
      <encoder>abc2xml version 268</encoder>
      <software>https://wim.vree.org/svgParse/abc2xml.html</software>
      <encoding-date>2026-07-21</encoding-date>
    </encoding>
    <source>Music source: The Hymnal (Episcopal), 1940 hymn 80 listed without copyright.  Although the setting is usually attributed to Douglas,
who as on the 1940 hymnal committee, no credit or copyright is called out in the hymnal as it is onother hymns.
The 1940 copyright on this hymnal was never renewed.</source>
    <miscellaneous>
      <miscellaneous-field name="lyrics">6.Were you there when God raised Him from the tomb?
Were you there when God raised Him from the tomb?
Oh! Sometimes it causes me to tremble, tremble, tremble.
Were you there when God raised Him from the tomb?</miscellaneous-field>
    </miscellaneous>
  </identification>
